  "texts": [
    "Self-motivating her actions, she draws on world-side events (i.e., happenings from her social system -the group).",
    "Eventually, these subtle shifts of bodily dynamics allow Paula to re-evoke her absent group members in observable ways, as I will later show.",
    "In line 10, she brings her absent group members 'at hand' (in Heideggerian terms) in a more obvious way -for herself and the interviewer.",
    "As she continues her story, she uses her body more directly.",
    "The way in which the interplay of body dynamics enables the re-evoking of past encounters becomes more apparent."
